<subSubSection id="48D355CA8EA7FF2948A75339FE2BFA65" pageId="233" pageNumber="234" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418EA7FF2948A75339FAEBFA81" blockId="233.[151,1438,1045,1682]" pageId="233" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538EA7FF2948A75339FE02FBDD" bold="true" box="[151,423,1045,1070]" pageId="233" pageNumber="234">Description of Female.</emphasis>
Fully winged; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48EA7FF294A995339FC96FBDD" box="[681,819,1045,1069]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="3.2" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="233" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="2.75" valueMax="3.2" valueMin="2.3">2.3–3.2 mm</quantity>
. Head black; antenna yellow, except segments 8–10 or 9–10 brown; mesosoma black; metasoma black-brown; legs testaceous, except metacoxa brown. Antenna clavate. Head dull, hairy, reticulate rugose; occasionally vertex with two oblique keels connecting posterior ocelli to occipital carina; face narrow, very converging towards clypeus; occipital carina complete; POL = 4; OL = 3; OOL = 4; OPL = 6; TL = 4; mandible with four teeth progressing larger from anterior one to posterior. Scutum dull, hairy, reticulate rugose and sculptured by many longitudinal keels. Notauli absent. Scutellum and metanotum dull, hairy, finely punctate. Propodeum reticulate rugose; posterior surface with two complete longitudinal keels. Fore wing with two dark transverse bands; stigmal vein slightly curved (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48EA7FF294B66523DFC60FAD9" box="[854,965,1297,1321]" captionStart="PLATE 66" captionStartId="227.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[185,1396,226,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-73@227.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="227" captionText="PLATE 66. A. Male genitalia, holotype. B, C. Female stigmal veins. D, E. Chelae, holotypes. A. Bocchus levis (from Olmi 1991). B, D. B. muluensis (from Olmi 1984). C, E. B. pedunculatus (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.19 mm for A, 0.41 mm for B and C, 0.13 mm for D and 0.16 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278607" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278607/files/figure.png" pageId="233" pageNumber="234">Plate 66B</figureCitation>
); pterostigma short and narrow. Protarsal segments 
<quantity id="C731ABA48EA7FF2949365219FEEBFABD" box="[262,334,1333,1357]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.35" metricValueMax="10.16" metricValueMin="2.54" pageId="233" pageNumber="234" unit="in" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4 in</quantity>
following proportions: 14:3:3:12. Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48EA7FF294BB45219FC56FABD" box="[900,1011,1333,1357]" captionStart="PLATE 66" captionStartId="227.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[185,1396,226,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-73@227.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="227" captionText="PLATE 66. A. Male genitalia, holotype. B, C. Female stigmal veins. D, E. Chelae, holotypes. A. Bocchus levis (from Olmi 1991). B, D. B. muluensis (from Olmi 1984). C, E. B. pedunculatus (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.19 mm for A, 0.41 mm for B and C, 0.13 mm for D and 0.16 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278607" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278607/files/figure.png" pageId="233" pageNumber="234">Plate 66D</figureCitation>
) with one row of six–seven teeth and one bristle. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48EA7FF294A195275FD32FA81" box="[553,663,1369,1393]" captionStart="PLATE 66" captionStartId="227.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[185,1396,226,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-73@227.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="227" captionText="PLATE 66. A. Male genitalia, holotype. B, C. Female stigmal veins. D, E. Chelae, holotypes. A. Bocchus levis (from Olmi 1991). B, D. B. muluensis (from Olmi 1984). C, E. B. pedunculatus (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.19 mm for A, 0.41 mm for B and C, 0.13 mm for D and 0.16 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278607" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278607/files/figure.png" pageId="233" pageNumber="234">Plate 66D</figureCitation>
) with one preapical lamella and one bristle. Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418EA7FF2948F75251FE2BFA65" blockId="233.[151,1438,1045,1682]" box="[199,398,1405,1429]" pageId="233" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538EA7FF2948F75251FEAEFA65" bold="true" box="[199,267,1405,1429]" pageId="233" pageNumber="234">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
